docs.abstract: Hundreds of thousands of AstraZeneca doses are sitting unopened as many Germans reject the vaccine over fears it is “second-class” compared to the one developed by BioNTech and Pfizer.
docs.snippet: Hundreds of thousands of AstraZeneca doses are sitting unopened as many Germans reject the vaccine over fears it is “second-class” compared to the one developed by BioNTech and Pfizer.
docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN — At the start of the year, many Germans were complaining about a shortage of coronavirus vaccines that could free them from onerous lockdowns and limited social lives. Just weeks later, many are now upset that they’re not getting the vaccine they want.

headline.main: Germans Clamor for Covid Vaccines, but Shun AstraZeneca’s Offering
headline.print_headline: They Wanted a Covid Vaccine. But Not That One.

docs.abstract: As the United States continues its campaign to immunize every eligible American adult, we explore an overlooked question: When will children get the vaccine?
docs.snippet: As the United States continues its campaign to immunize every eligible American adult, we explore an overlooked question: When will children get the vaccine?
docs.lead_paragraph: For American adults, the conclusion of the pandemic appears to be on the horizon. The end of summer 2021 has been earmarked as the time by which most adults will be vaccinated. But still remaining is the often-overlooked question of vaccinations for children.

docs.abstract: We might be able to achieve normalcy by summer. Our leaders should embrace the possibility.
docs.snippet: We might be able to achieve normalcy by summer. Our leaders should embrace the possibility.
docs.lead_paragraph: Christmas of 2021: According to both President Biden and Dr. Anthony Fauci, together the two most prominent voices on public health in America right now, that’s when we can hope for a return to normalcy, the beginning of life after the emergency.

docs.abstract: Even within political parties, governors were taking different approaches as they tried to balance public health guidance with residents’ eagerness to get back to normal life.
docs.snippet: Even within political parties, governors were taking different approaches as they tried to balance public health guidance with residents’ eagerness to get back to normal life.
docs.lead_paragraph: Despite President Biden’s sharp criticism of Texas and Mississippi for abruptly removing mask mandates, states and cities are aggressively going their own ways on Covid-19 restrictions as they decide when and how to reopen their economies.

headline.main: As Biden Urges Caution on Covid, Governors Split on How Fast to Reopen
headline.print_headline: States Go Own Ways on Covid Rules

byline.original: By Julie Bosman, Michael D. Shear and Reid J. Epstein

docs.abstract: The growing attraction of short-term real estate loans during the pandemic is making it easier to borrow to refurbish properties.
docs.snippet: The growing attraction of short-term real estate loans during the pandemic is making it easier to borrow to refurbish properties.
docs.lead_paragraph: The pandemic forced owners of hotels, malls and office buildings to adjust almost overnight to a harsh reality in which millions of Americans were no longer traveling, shopping at stores or going into offices. It also depressed the vast market where such companies raise money for their commercial real estate projects.

headline.main: Landlords Eager for Covid-Era Revamps Are Finding Hungry Investors
